sidux-settings-xfce (1.7) unstable; urgency=low

  * redo the dodgy on providing useful defaults for xfce 4.6
    - non-conflicting files go into etc/xdg/
    - conflicting, or likely to conflict go into usr/share/sidux-settings-xfce/ 
       and get pulled into live user profile by desktop-defaults preseed script
  * remove no longer used mcs_settings dir
  * add sidux-browser-*.rc launcher
  * take settings back to almost debian defaults, panel layout, toolbars
  * autostart/* handled in desktop-defaults preseeding already, revert
  * splash setting handled in desktop-defaults, revert
  * wallpaper setting handled in desktop defaults, revert
  * panels.xml - set correct launcher id for sidux-browser
  * rename siduxbrowser just in case extra dashes cause a problem
  * remove no longer existing autostart from debian/install

